results.title: The Red Skull in: Turnabout
results.description: The Skull is a valet in a fancy hotel catering to Americans and other unholy swine in the hell the Cosmic Cube has created for him; After a lethal encounter with Captain America, the Skull wins his way free of the Cube's influence and returns to the real world.

results.title: Captain America (1998) #15
results.description: Iron Man brings Cap his missing shield which is broken in pieces; The Red Skull has internalized the Cosmic Cube giving him ultimate power; The Watcher shows Cap a future controlled by the Skull.

results.title: Red Glare
results.description: The Red Skull declares survival of the fittest in America and begins his plans for world domination; The Watcher tells Cap that the only way to stop the Skull is to kill him; The Skull reverts Cap to his scrawny pre-super soldier self.

results.title: A Peek at the Future of Captain America
Captain America (1998) #17
results.description: Cap takes the Watcher's advice and kills the Red Skull; Korvac reveals his duplicity in masterminding the plot to obtain the Skull's power.

results.title: 1/2 Man, 1/2 Desk: The Life and Times of Korvac
Captain America (1998) #18
results.description: In the 31st Century where Korvac reigns supreme, Cap foils his plans through countless re-boots of the time-stream; Korvac returns himself and Cap to the instant before Cap killed the Skull and Korvac stole his power.

results.title: The Life Story of Cap's Shield (or Everything You Wanted to Know to Enjoy Issue #20)
Captain America (1998) #19
results.description: When Korvac returns them to the moment before Cap killed the Red Skull, Cap refuses to do it again and tries to find another way to beat both of his infinitely powerful enemies.

results.title: Captain America (1998) #21
results.description: Cap's broken shield has created a vibranium cancer that threatens to destroy all vibranium on earth; Klaw escapes from his vibranium cell.

results.title: Sgt. Fury in Bloodline Part 2
results.description: Fury and the Howlers escape Blood's lair with the help of one of his vampiric victims.

results.title: Captain America (1998) #22
results.description: Klaw tries to stop Cap from averting the vibranium wave that is about to destroy all the vibranium in Wakanda but only succeeds in fixing Cap's broken shield.

results.title: Captain America (1998) #25
results.description: Fury and a general disappear in Idaho, and Cap and the Falcon are sent out to find them but get themselves captured by the Hate Monger's new outfit.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 2: Feel the Rush
Captain America (1998) #26
results.description: Cap and Fury escape Hate Monger's death trap in time to see him launch two anthrax missiles to which the Falcon and the general are tied.

results.title: Captain America (1998) #27
results.description: Cap, Falcon and Fury foil the Hate Monger's plans to start a war with anthrax.

results.title: Duel
results.description: S.H.I.E.L.D. helps Cap look for Batroc, who has stolen a disk of info.  When Cap confronts Batroc, he realizes who Batroc is working for.  Meanwhile, Nick Fury finds someone.

results.title: Candor
results.description: As Cap dangles over a nuclear warhead, we learn the motivation for The Answer's actions.  And a secret is found out.

results.title: Conclusions
results.description: Before Cap and Connie can discuss what went on last issue, the Taskmaster's goons capture Cap and the Taskmaster himself works Cap over.  Meanwhile, Connie makes a decision.

results.title: America Lost Part I of IV
results.description: Nick Fury visits Cap to see what's up with him. While there, he lets Cap know that S.H.I.E.L.D. is determined to find the Helicarrier.  Meanwhile, a hate crime in Louisiana sparks a suspicion that maybe the Red Skull is involved.  And preparations are made for a funeral...

results.title: America Lost Part II of IV
results.description: Cap finds the Helicarrier in the Gulf of Mexico and comes face-to-face with the Red Skull.  Nick Fury tries to find out more about the hate crimes going on in Louisiana and meets the instigator.  Meanwhile, more people gather for a funeral...

results.title: America Lost Part III of IV
results.description: Namor joins the fight as Cap and Sharon Carter find out what is the plan by infiltrating the Helicarrier.  Nick Fury is taken prisoner by the Red Skull and we find out who the Skull's partner is.  The casket is brought and all of the mourners are almost ready for the funeral...

results.title: America Lost Part IV of IV
results.description: The conclusion to the "America Lost" storyline.  And a funeral for a friend.

results.title: Closure
results.description: Steve and Sam try to relax.  Steve tries to bring some closure with Connie.  And Captain America realizes who his true love is.
